cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically parsing human poses in images. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques, such as Latent Support Vector Machine, to learn visual symbols, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also proposes an efficient approach to estimating human poses in images, which could fall under cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
